<br>
I'm sorry I feel the need to address this.<br>
<br>
You're comparing someone in full ToV armour to someone in Hate armour.<br>
<br>
OF COURSE they will have higher ac/more hp than someone with &quot;lesser&quot; armour.<br>
<br>
Compare a Ranger in full PoF armour to a warrior in full PoH armour. The warrior will *still* have higher ac/more hp.<br>
<br>
You can't compare apples and oranges.<br>
<br>
Everyone in my guild is in full SS quest armour. The warriors have higher ac/more hp than the Rangers or the Monks.<br>
<br>
If someone spends 50 hours a week playing EQ, and someone spends 5 hours a week playing EQ, why should the person that spends 1/10th of the time playing have equal gear and abilities?<br>
<br>
This game rewards you the more time you spend at it. You can like it, accept it, or not. But don't then complain when someone who spends 10x's the amount of time you do has better stuff.<br>
<br>
P.S.<br>
<br>
I agree warriors need better tauning abilities. I also think that AA != Balance. Not now, not ever. Upgrading Warrior taunt is very needed and I 110% agree it needs to be. But that's about all they need, IMO. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uelawnah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elawnah</A> at: 9/28/02 10:05:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uheimdallazureguardian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heimdall Azureguardian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Dubious </span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#333333>(9/28/02 10:39:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Upgrades...</span><hr size=1> I disagree Elwanah.  I think Warriors need a baseline HP increase.<br>
<br>
This is copied from my post on the pet class rant.<br>
<br>
<br>
I honestly don't know the numbers- But for the sake of arguement- lets say monks and other non-warrior melee had 75-80% of Warrior hp. Lets say that warriors pre-buff had 2400 hp, and other melee had 2000. You add to lvl 49 buffs on top of that and warriors are probably at 3000, and the rest are at about 2600. At level 50 that's a big enough difference that warriors have a distinctive advantage that can reasonably be offset by other abilities if the other class is played right.<br>
<br>
Now at level 60, prebuff lets put warriors at 3100, and the rest at what 2600? (They're actually probably higher now, partly because more HP gear is available to them, and partly because they focus on hp gear more now.) Now add Raid buffs and warriors are at 5K, and non warriors are at 4700? The % difference has disappeared.<br>
<br>
Now try and factor in Block vs Parry and monks are suddenly looking very sweet indeed. Almost the same CH efficency based solely on hp, and better damage avoidance. Top that off with their higher damage output, and monks are my grind tank of choice boys and girls. FD pulling to group is just gravy.<br>
<br>
Any of you 60 melee want to put your HP numbers up so we can work with closer to accurate numbers? I was making Semi-educated guesses and I could be way off. <br>
<br>
