 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/ujaraxalle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaraxalle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#333333>(9/30/02 9:42:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Upgrades...</span><hr size=1> I agree that comparing myself to a monk/sk in TOV armor is unfair, and I'll put my point in a different way.<br>
<br>
Compare a warrior in hate/cobalt to a monk in Equivalent gear.  No complaints here, the roles of each class are defined, there's a rather large HP gap as their should be.  <br>
<br>
Compare a warrior in TOV armor against a monk in TOV armor.<br>
<br>
Notice something?  The HP gap is ever shrinking.  You showed yourself that monk gear has only about 150hp less than the warrior gear.  There are points in the game where a 53 monk would tank over me, why?  Better gear.  Do you ever see wizard roles disapearing because of gear?  What about clerics?  Do their roles disapear because of gear?  No.  They don't.  You don't see someone taking a druid as the nuker over a MB wizzy because the druid has a focus item and the wizzy doesn't.  The MB wizzy gets picked because he has MANABURN.  It's a class skill that he has.  Sure at 55 I'll have defensive, and I'm sure that it will make all the difference, but why can't the classes be balenced 1-60?  Beyond that defensive is level 55, there's not even an AA or level 60 disc to replace it.  I know that high end things start to balence out again, but seriously what about levels 1-59?  Even high end if you have anything less than uber gear, you aren't needed.  <br>
<br>
Warriors do indeed need a baseline increase in HP because the HP gap is decreasing.  Sure it's still there as you have proven, but you've also proven that it is shrinking.  It would also be nice to see a modifier on HP items for warriors, like a 10% bonus when you equip a piece of gear with HP on it.  That would fix what they broke when they decided to put All/All on gear with 125hp on it.  <br>
<br>
Another thing that you have to agree with is that the soloability of a warrior completely sucks.  I don't think there is a worse class out there when it comes to it.  Now they decided to increase clerics ability to solo?  On top if that they are giving a great solo class a great XP group and raid ability in giving CH to druids.  Not that warriors want solo-ability, but before we were given things to compensate, like being needed in grind groups.<br>
<br>
Couple the above with the fact that we aren't required in grind groups anymore, and that basicaly leaves us with one thing, Raids.  On raids we are unstackable.  If there are 2 warriors on a raid there is not point in adding more.  It would be smarter to add a monk/rogue for damage.  Maybe if the timers on our disc were lower we could have fun using them on a raid to make up for the damage output we lack in comparison (not a complaint, just a fact).  <br>
<br>
Just think about the class as a whole, we have no utility, can't solo, don't stack on raids, not needed in grind groups.  Can we tank, yeah, we can tank.  There are mobs where warriors are needed.  Still it's limiting.  It's saying that you must kill these mobs to be any great use in the game.  <br>
<br>
For warriors to have to reply on procs for aggro is also something that needs to be changed.  Again it forces warriors to rely on gear.  But it's been proven that taunt only succeeds 8% of the time on mobs that con even or higher.  Taunt only puts you at the top of the hate list if you succeed.  That's why you don't always get aggro from hitting taunt.  Ever notice that if someone grabs aggro from you and you try to get it back that it doesn't always hit you when you hit taunt?<br>
<br>
Again a lot of my points are from the view of the casual gamer, those who play 50/week and raid and are high end and uber, more power to you.  Most people don't have that much time.  I understand that someone playing 50hr/week is going to have better gear than me, but if I were to play a druid/wiz, I wouldn't be complaining about gear, or needing an upgrade.  <br>
<br>
Why can't I rely on me knowledge of the game and my class to be a good player?  You don't judge most other classes on their gear, but on how well they play their class.<br>
<br>
Warriors aren't the only ones to get the shaft, SK's are also very gear dependent.  IMO it's crap, we should have more class defining skills, like a monk/rogue's do.<br>
<br>
I am listening and yes, I can agree with some of the things that you are saying.  One of the things I am hearing is &quot;oh, be a high end warrior or don't be a warrior at all.&quot;  It's almost the same way for wizzies needing MB.  Some of my complaints are not just troubles with the warrior class, but with what the game has become in general.  I hope to see a positive change in the next expansion.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
