<br>
Would you take a Wizard without their good nukes, to a Wizard that can Manaburn?<br>
<br>
(Also of note. I wouldn't dare consider Manaburn a &quot;class skill&quot; askin to a /disc. You get a /disc automatically as you level. You have to be atleast level 59 *and* have at the bare minimum 27 AA points. Also, a Wizard with a bigger manapool [read: better gear] will do more damage with Manaburn than someone with lesser mana [read: worse gear]. As a final note, Manaburn isn't something you use in a grind situation when you can just give better sustained DPS via spells instead of Manaburn.)<br>
<br>
Would you take a 55 Cleric with no Epic to a 55 Cleric with their Epic?<br>
<br>
Would you take a Shaman without Torpor to a Shaman with Torpor? Replace Torpor with Focus and ask the question again.<br>
<br>
*Every* class has become gear reliant. Be it actual items you equip or spells.<br>
<br>
If you answered yes to those questions, then it shouldn't matter that a Monk in full up-to-date Luclin gear can out-tank you in Kunark era gear.<br>
<br>
Have you ever been rejected from a raid because of your gear? If you have, perhaps you need to find a better guild. If not, then why are you complaining? You're still *needed*.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Even high end if you have anything less than uber gear, you aren't needed.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That statement is just completly false. Or is this turning into an uber guild vs. casual guild debate?<br>
<br>
Plain and simple: This game is focused on gear to achieve any of the &quot;high end&quot; goals. You can like it, or not. If you don't like it you don't have to participate in it.<br>
<br>
Then again, there are goals set by the more casual gamers that don't focus on the high end goals of the game. That's perfectly fine, too. You play the game the way you want to play it. But don't then complain that you don't have xxx. You made the choice not to. Don't let it bother you and have fun with the game reguardless.<br>
<br>
Warriors need a bump in their taunting abilities. But that's about all I see, really. The HP gap, even if it is lower than it once was, is still fine because the Warrior still comes out on top by *atleast* 1khp, if not more. 1khp dosen't seem like alot but it matters.<br>
<br>
Just relax, play the game the way you want and have fun.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/udmspike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DMSpike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00bie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 9:35:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Warrior Upgrades...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> if you spent the time that you type about eq, playing eq... I bet you'd be ubah!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Quite true my friend, I post from work between assignments.  Too bad I'm stuck on windows NT or I would play between assignments.  <br>
<br>
I've never been rejected from a raid because of my gear, but alas my guild has folded.  I hope to find I still don't get rejected in grind groups or raids simply because there are no guildies around.<br>
<br>
As to the matter of the shrinking HP gap.  Yes, there is still a 1k difference between a high end warrior and SK.  While this number is sufficient to many, the % of the hitpoint gap is indeed shrinking.  What if in this next expansion that 1k remains constant?  10k warrior vs. 9k SK?  Anyone can see that 7k vs 8k is a better ratio than 9k vs 10k.  Right now things are still in balence, although the gap isn't what it once was.  <br>
<br>
My concerns are mainly for a screwed up PoP expansion, where shields block as well as our defensive disc, we're outdamaged by bards and to taunt warriors need Uber_taunt_weapon_001 which cost 600k just to keep up.  OK, that a joke and to an extreme, but you get the idea. <br>
<br>
 <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Even high end if you have anything less than uber gear, you aren't needed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In this I was referring to the AC/HP req. that some guilds have.  A monk/rogue doesn't have to worry about this.  If a monk is a good puller and knows how to split mobs, does anyone care what their AC/HP's are? (To a certain degree, I'm sure no one wants a nekked monk pulling.)<br>
<br>
<br>
For me, the bazaar has been incredibly beneficial.  I have equipment now that I never would have dreamed I would have.  It should be fairly easy for me to level, even solo once I'm done re-tooling.  <br>
<br>
I must say that this has been a rather productive debate.  There have been a few good points made that have changed my mind a bit.  I haven't heard anything that's been said be total BS, rather a something from a different point of view that I simply don't completely agree with.  At this point I don't think anyone is going to change anyone else's minds.  Thanks for a what I would call a good thread.  We will all see what happens in PoP.<br>
<br>
<br>
-Jaraxalle<br>
