The MB wizzy gets picked because he has MANABURN. It's a class skill that he has<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A manaburn wizzy, perhaps, and then only in certain situations. I know a few wizards, and if you want to talk about a class that has a hard time getting a group, it's wizards. <br>
<br>
Can someone replace a wizard if they have good gear? Yes, just about any melee, particularly a rogue or monk.<br>
<br>
Get a rogue with a 14 damage (or higher) piercer, and their Backstab will create similar (or greater)damage to a non-manaburn wizard. Add to that the fact that they don't get resisted, and have more ac/hp, and are therefore easier to keep alive, and many people would take them over a wizard.<br>
<br>
Similarly, I often see druids taken over wizzies as nukers, bacause they can also snare and sow. <br>
<br>
Honestly, I have actually seen a SHAMAN who could outtank the tank that was in a group I was in once. Of course, the tank had crappy gear (still had some FS plate on in the 40's, and slow weapons) while the Shaman had awesome gear. The shammy had higher ac/more hp, and could hold aggro with spells. Not that this will usually happen, just showing that gear makes a HUGE difference. <p>Xaanru <br>
